# Phase 1 pre-scoring model (snipe-screen).
# Base: Qwen3 4B Instruct 2507 at q8_0 — benchmarked 2026-07-17 against
# qwen2.5:7b-instruct-q5_K_M and qwen3:8b on 8 labeled JDs (see batch/bench):
# the 7B collapsed scores to 2.6 and fabricated hard stops in 7/8 runs; the 8B
# judged best but spills 20-25% to CPU on 6 GB (~60s/offer); the 4B matches the
# 8B on easy calls at ~13s/offer fully on-GPU. Its senior-role optimism is
# absorbed by the deterministic seniorityCaps() gate in ollama-scorer.mjs.
# Phase 2 uses snipe-eval; Phase 3 uses snipe-cv (coder base).
#
# Build:  ollama create snipe-screen -f batch/Modelfile.snipe-screen
FROM qwen3:4b-instruct-2507-q8_0

# All layers on GPU (~4.4 GB weights — fits 6 GB with KV headroom)
PARAMETER num_gpu 99

# Note: KV cache quantization is set via environment variable, not Modelfile:
#   OLLAMA_KV_CACHE_TYPE=q8_0 ollama serve
